<subSubSection id="9A3071EFFCB09D4E6B01B6C0DCF356AC" pageId="16" pageNumber="55" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3D0ED0E4ECCA3AFF0D5FCB1B80D2787F" pageId="16" pageNumber="55">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="36417500877CBF54EFC812CE18628A2A" pageId="16" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="C9A3A9C28A16B995E3457D398B76984F" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="55">vagina</emphasis>
(Latin) = sheath. Possibly referring to the conspicuous leaf-sheaths, a feature that is common to most of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
